Freedom Day, celebrated on April 27 every year, commemorates the symbolic fall of Apartheid in South Africa as the first democratic elections were held on that day in 1994. It is also intended to be a celebration of freedom. But what exactly does freedom mean? HeraldLIVE s Deneesha Pillay and Annelisa Swana asked school pupils from around Port Elizabeth what they thought. Related Share on Facebook Share Share on Twitter Tweet Share on Google Plus Share